<HEAD>
<TITLE>Microscopy UK / MICSCAPE - 3D Stereo Microscopy : Insects</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00">

<a name="top">

<P>
<center><h1>3D Flea</h1></center>
<p>

<center><IMG SRC="3dflea.jpg"></center>
<p>
<h4>
This is a <em>true</em> 3D image of a flea. The depth of the subject
into the physical slide is very thin causing only a very slight presence
of depth in the sampled image here.
<p>
It was obtained by moving a  specimen slide under a microscope
along the X-axis and taking a video 'still' of the subject twice. Both images were
used as left and right views, and then combined using <A href="3dads.html#dv">Double Vision</A> software.
</h4>
