<HEAD>
<TITLE>Microscopy UK / MICSCAPE - 3D Stereo Microscopy : Nettle Flower</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00">

<a name="top">

<P>
<center><h1>Nettle Flower</h1></center>
<p>

<center><IMG SRC="3dnet_s.gif"></center>
<p>
<h4>
A nettle picked from my garden in England during Springtime. You just
won't accept the beauty of this little plant until you see it close
up in 3D. Visit the <a href="../../gallery/fractal.html">Fractal Imagery Gallery</A> via Microscopy UK front screen
to get a fantastic close-up look. The ruler on the left indicates size in millimeters.

<p>
This image was created by capture with a video camera. A left shot was taken then the camcorder 
was moved to the right a little for the second shot. The two images were 
combined using <A href="3dads.html#dv">Double Vision</A> software.

</h4>
