<TITLE>MICSCAPE - 3D Stereo Microscopy : Micro-fossils</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00">

<a name="top">

<P>
<center><h1>3D Foraminifea Spiroloculina Camaliculata </h1></center>
<p>

<center><IMG SRC="3dfor2.jpg" width=235 height=266></center>
<h4>
Foraminifea are a group of minute creatures, chiefly marine, belonging to the 
sub-kingdom Protozoa. The lime in the Earth's crust and the ooze of ocean beds
are mainly made up of shells from these creatures. Magnification approx. 100x.

</h4>


