<HEAD><TITLE>MICROSCOPY UK - MICSCAPE ARTICLE: Why Microscopy for Webmasters</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#0000FF" LINK="#000000" VLINK="#888888">
<CENTER>
<STRONG>
&reg <FONT SIZE=6>Micscape Magazine Article</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=8> WHY... MICROSCOPY?</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>by Maurice Smith.</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=2>(Help for Webmasters)</FONT>
</STRONG>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="BLUE">
Many web sites with information on Amateur Science and related subjects often forget to mention
<FONT SIE=4 COLOR="RED"> Amateur Microscopy.</FONT><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="BLUE"> That's okay, we forgive you ;)
<P>
The problem is that most people don't even realise that microscopy is itself an amateur
science study area. Maybe you would like to help change that?
<P>
Why not lift the following 4 pages from our site and place them on your one. All that we ask
is that you don't change their content, except of course to add the appropriate links so your own readers
can flick back to your own internal index.html or contents page. If you load all 4 pages then you can also 
remove the explicit part of the URL which links the four pages together at our site, so they link together
and cross reference each other locally on your site: speeds up the loading.
<P>
All the pages have explicit links to pick up the images direct from our site. Please leave these in.
If you want to grab the pictures and load the whole article complete with images locally to speed up
access by your readers, please <a href="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">drop me a note</A> letting me know
this is what you would like to do. For the other options, don't worry about asking, you have our permission
as long as you are willing to leave in the relevant copyright notices and their inherent link to our site.
<P>
You could just load page 1 from the list below onto your site if you want the least time-consuming
solution to help out. The Page 1 html contains everything ready to work with the pages and images 
you leave here on our site. Go on... help out this area of Amateur Science and give us a hand at promoting it 
to others as a worthwhile study area.
<P>
<br>
<center><FONT SIZE=6 COLOR="RED">THE FOUR PAGES</FONT>
<br>
You need to download the following 4 pages by clicking on them and saving them to your PC:-
<p>
<a href="HTTP://www.microscopy-uk.org.uk/mag/articles/whymic2.html">Page 1 (whymic2.html)</A><br>
<a href="HTTP://www.microscopy-uk.org.uk/mag/articles/whymic2a.html">Page 2 (whymic2a.html)</A><br>
<a href="HTTP://www.microscopy-uk.org.uk/mag/articles/whymic2b.html">Page 3 (whymic2b.html)</A><br>
<a href="HTTP://www.microscopy-uk.org.uk/mag/articles/whymic2x.html">Plea   (whymic2x.html) This Page!</A><br>
</center>
<br>
<P>
Cheers! <strong><em>Maurice Smith of Microscopy-UK</em></strong>
