<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Web Developer/Programmer</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFF">
<IMG SRC="../gif/jtoheaderSmall.gif" ALIGN=left >

<BR clear=left><BR><BR>
<H1><CENTER><H4><FONT COLOR="450000"> <FONT SIZE=5>W</FONT>ORLD <FONT SIZE=5>W</FONT>IDE <FONT SIZE=5>W</FONT>EB <FONT SIZE=5>D</FONT>EVELOPER / <FONT SIZE=5>P</FONT>ROGRAMMER</H4></FONT></CENTER>
</H1>
<BR>

<H4><FONT COLOR="450000"> <FONT SIZE=5>A</FONT>BOUT <FONT SIZE=5>J</FONT>OIN <FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>OGETHER</H4></FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Join Together is a national resource center supporting communities working on public health and related issues. Funded principally by a grant from <A HREF="http://www.rwjf.org">The Robert Wood Johnson Foundation</A> to the <A HREF="http://www-busph.bu.edu/">Boston University School of
Public Health</A>, Join Together Online operates multiple Web
sites (see: <A HREF="/">http://www.jointogether.org</A>
and <A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org/">http://www.quitnet.org</A>) designed to serve as an online workplace for communities nationwide.  Join Together Online is ready to greatly expand its Web and database server operations in response to growing demand for <A HREF="/demo/index.html">sophisticated Web publishing services</A> by national and state-wide organizations.  </BLOCKQUOTE>

<H4><FONT COLOR="450000"><FONT SIZE=5>A</FONT>BOUT <FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>HIS <FONT SIZE=5>P</FONT>OSITION</H4></FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE>The <B>Web Developer/Programmer</B> (based in our Boston office)
will be a key member of our Web Development Team which is responsible for
the development of a growing number of Web sites operating on in-house Web
and database servers off a direct link to the Internet.  This is a unique
opportunity for a skilled programmer to make an enormous contribution to
the work of many non-profit organizations dedicated to building healthier,
safer communities nationwide.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H4><FONT COLOR="450000"><FONT SIZE=5>R</FONT>ESPONSIBILITIES</H4></FONT>
<UL>
<LI> Design and develop custom database applications to support Web publishing
activities of multiple organizations.
<LI> Site management and administration.
<LI> Write and edit HTML 2 and commercial enhancements.
</UL>

<H4><FONT COLOR="450000"><FONT SIZE=5>S</FONT>KILL <FONT SIZE=5>I</FONT>N / <FONT SIZE=5>K</FONT>NOWLEDGE <FONT SIZE=5>O</FONT>F </FONT>(as many of the following as possible):</H4>
<UL>
<LI> Database systems and programming (familiarity with SQL and Tango
a big plus).
<LI> Internet protocols, TCP/IP, HTTP, low level networking, etc.
<LI> Windows NT and Macintosh operating systems.
<LI> Web servers.
<LI> HTML authoring, including tables, frames and Java-script.
<LI> DNS, FTP, SMTP and POP mail servers and back-up, remote paging and
rebooting systems.
</UL>

<BR>
Boston University prohibits discrimination against any individual on the
basis of race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, physical or mental
handicap, marital, parental, or veteran status.  This position will remain
open until we find the right person.  <BR>
<P><CENTER><FONT COLOR="450000"><B>Send inquiries to:</B></FONT><BR>
Chris Cartter (<A HREF="mailto:chris@jointogether.org">chris@jointogether.org</A>)<BR>
Join Together<BR>
Boston University School of Public Health</CENTER>
</BODY>
</HTML>
