    <HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Press Releases</TITLE></HEAD><!-Default-><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/newsban.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/newsban.gif" WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75"BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/jto/news/news.html">News &amp; Communications</A> | <A HREF="/news/jto/Latest_News.qry">News</A>| <A HREF="/news/releases/Latest_News.qry?PressReleases=True&Summaries=On&Max=150&Last=30">Releases</A>| <A HREF="/go.qry?gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org:7003/11/news">Archives</A> | <A HREF="/URLs/JTO/URL_Show.qry?header=news&filter=drugs&Category=Media&Summaries=on">Links</A></FONT></CENTER><p><TABLE WIDTH = "90%" CELLSPACING = "0"><TR><TD WIDTH = "60%"><h2>Join Together Online Named A Top Health-Related Web Site</h2></TD><TD></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN = "2"><FONT COLOR = "BLACK"><A HREF="http://www.gii-awards.com"><IMG SRC="/gif/NII/NIISq_FHeal.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH="116" HEIGHT="101" BORDER="0"></A>
November 15, 1996<br><br>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br><br>Contact: <br>Chris Cartter<br>Join Together<br>617-437-1500<br><a href=mailto:chris@jointogether.org">chris@jointogether.org</a><br><br>Donna Ceparano/Fleishman-Hillard (NII contact)<br>212-265-9150 Ext.2242 <br><a href="mailto:ceparand@fleishman.com">ceparand@fleishman.com</a><br><br>
<H3>Join Together Online Named One of the <br>Nation&#146;s Six Leading Health-Related Web Sites</H3> <B>NII AWARDS PROGRAM ANNOUNCES FINALISTS IN SECOND ANNUAL COMPETITION TO RECOGNIZE OUTSTANDING USES OF COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGIES</B><br><br>LOS ANGELES, CA - Join Together Online, a Web site devoted to helping communities reduce substance abuse, has reached the Finalist level in the 1996 National Information Infrastructure Awards (NII) program, the world's leading forum for the recognition of extraordinary achievement on the Internet and information highway.<br><br>Join Together Online is one of six Finalists in the NII&#146;s Health category.  In all, there are 60 Finalists &#151; chosen from a field of nearly 1,000 nominees &#151; in the NII Program's search for the country's most creative and beneficial uses of communication technologies. The Program recognizes work in 10 different categories that touch on all areas of America's work, play and community life.<br><br>&#147;Every day parents, elected officials, police officers, ministers, teachers and kids from around the nation turn to Join Together Online for help in addressing the problems associated with substance abuse &#151; the nation&#146;s number one health care problem ," said David L. Rosenbloom, director of Join Together.<br><br>Join Together Online (<A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A>) is a resource center and meeting place for community-based organizations working to reduce the harms associated with the use of illicit drugs, excessive alcohol and tobacco.  Join Together, a project of the <A HREF="http://www-busph.bu.edu/">Boston University School of Public Health</A>, is principally funded by grants from <A HREF="http://www.rwjf.org">The Robert Wood Johnson Foundation</A>.  With over 14,000 documents and many interactive databases online, Join Together Online is the world&#146;s largest online substance abuse resource center. <br><br>" Join Together&#146;s status as an NII Finalist is an outstanding achievement and acknowledgement of its creativity in using electronic communications to solve problems," said James Hake, Chairman of the NII Awards Program. "Join Together Online serves as an example of the kind of leadership and dedication that are critical to our continued development as an information era society."<br><br>The winners will be announced at a major awards ceremony to be held December 3, in New York City. A complete list of Finalists is available at the NII Website, <A HREF="http://www.gii-awards.com">http://www.gii-awards.com</A>.<br><br>Nominees in the NII Awards Program range from powerful corporations, to entrepreneuers, to grassroots community organizations to individuals. They are competing for awards in Arts and Entertainment, Business, Children, Community, Education, Next Generation, Government and Health, and in two special awards, the NII Public Access Awards, sponsored by the U.S. Postal Service, and the NII Telecollaboration Award, sponsored by AT&T. Categories are presided over by separate panels of judges comprised of recognized experts in each area.<br><br>This year's NII Awards Finalists display an impressive range of talents and solutions. Participants include publishers of online magazines and newspapers, designers of children- and teenager-oriented World Wide Web sites, manufacturers of semiconductors, teachers, scientists and community organizers.<br><br>The program is made possible by more than 70 corporate and media sponsors, including IBM, one of the pioneering organizations of the Information Age, and the sponsor of this year's Awards ceremony.<br><br>Only two years old, the NII Awards Program has emerged as the most important competition for the recognition of information highway uses, and has won praise from a broad range of industry and community leaders, including Vice President Al Gore, who cited the NII's efforts to reward and showcase these especially beneficial uses of the information highway.<br><br>For more information about the NII Awards, go to <A HREF="http://www.gii-awards.com">http://www.gii-awards.com</A>. To visit Join Together Online, go to <A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A>.<br><br># # #<br></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><FONT SIZE = "-1"><TABLE WIDTH ="100%"><TR><TD WIDTH="30%"><B>Date:   </B>11/15/1996</TD></TR></TABLE></FONT><P><I>Distributed by <A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">Join Together Online</A>.</I></P>    <P><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/MapServe/footer.gif"WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle  ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A></FONT><BR><BR><HR><FONT SIZE="-1">Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="/">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></B></CENTER></BODY>
