<TD VALIGN="TOP">



<FONT COLOR=BLACK>

<H2>Features & Headlines<HR WIDTH=60% HEIGHT=5 ALIGN=left NOSHADE></H2>

</FONT>



<B>Follow the Money</B><BR>

<FONT SIZE="-1">This week's Funding News highlights: more than <A HREF="/posting/FundingNews.qry?function=detail&FundingNews_Aid=635">$4.4 billion available in federal AOD funding</A>; the 1995-97 <A HREF="/posting/FundingNews.qry?function=detail&FundingNews_Aid=636">Federal AOD Budget</A>; and several <A HREF="/posting/FundingNews.qry?function=LatestNews&Max=150&Last=60&ArticleType=2">new federal grant announcements</A> for substance abuse and related programs.</FONT><BR><BR>



<B>Soros Explains Marijuana Position</B><BR>

<FONT SIZE="-1">In a Washington Post <A HREF="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/WPlate/1997-02/02/083L-020297-idx.html">op-ed</A> this week, financier turned philanthropist George Soros explains why he pumped a $1 million into medical marijuana propositions in <A HREF="/news/jto/Show_News.qry?News_uid=9277">CA</A> and <A HREF="/news/jto/Show_News.qry?News_uid=9275">AZ</A>.  Soros, widely <A HREF="/news/jto/Show_News.qry?News_uid=9967">criticized</A> for his challenge to current drug policy, believes that "criminalizing drug abuse does more harm than good, blocking effective treatment and incarcerating far too many people."</FONT><BR><BR>



<B>Marketing Prevention to Managed Care</B><BR>

<FONT SIZE="-1">Our <A HREF="/posting/FundingNews.qry?function=detail&FundingNews_Aid=628">newest community funding profile</A> shows how substance abuse prevention programs can access an important--and emerging--funding source by taking advantage of managed care's interest in reducing the demand for health services.</FONT><BR><BR>



<B>Injected THC Found Not To Cause Cancer</B><BR>

<FONT SIZE="-1">A previously unpublished federal study concluded that THC, the main ingredient in marijuana, <A HREF="/news/jto/Show_News.qry?News_uid=9944">does not cause cancer when injected</A> in laboratory animals. The findings call into question  the government's contention that marijuana is carcinogenic. Also, in an editorial, <A HREF="http://www.nejm.org/publicM/1997/0336/0005/0366/1.htm">"Federal Foolishness and Marijuana"</A>, the New England Journal of Medicine calls on the government to reclassify marijuana so it can be used for medical purposes.

</FONT><BR><BR>





<CENTER>

<TABLE BORDER=3 CELLPADDING=1 >

<TR>



        <TD>

        <CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1"><B><A HREF="/jto/webhead.html">Web Developers Needed</A></B><BR>

The JTO Web Team needs <FONT COLOR="RED" >red hot</FONT> talent. </FONT></CENTER>

        </TD>  

        



</TR>

</TABLE>

</CENTER>







</TD>



	

<TD WIDTH=10 ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/vert_lin.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE WIDTH="1" HEIGHT="230">

</TD>



<TD WIDTH="30%"  VALIGN="CENTER" >

<A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org"><IMG SRC="/gif/quitnetSmall.gif" ALT="The QuitNet" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0></A><BR>



If you're a smoker struggling to quit or a smoking cessation counselor looking for the latest news, the <A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org">QuitNet</A> is an invaluable tool containing: 

<UL TYPE=DISC>

	<LI><A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org/QuitTools/Interactive/Tools.html">interactive quitting quides</A><BR>

	<LI>a comprehensive <A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org/Library/">library</A><BR>

	<LI><A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org/Library/Links/Index.html">links</A> to related Web sites<BR>

	<LI><A HREF="http://www.quitnet.org/Talk/conf_msgs.qry?Conference_ID=10&conf=8">The QuitStop</A>, a smoker support group. <BR><BR>

</UL>



<B><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="#896b29">Join Together Online</FONT></B><BR><A HREF="/news/releases/Show_News.qry?News_uid=9347">has been named</A> one of the nation's top health Web sites according to the National Information Infrastructure Awards. <BR><BR><BR>



















<BR>

</TD>

</TR>

</TABLE>













