<TITLE>Drinking and Driving</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>

<BR>

<center><H2>Drinking and Driving</H2></center>


Alcohol-related crashes are a leading cause of death for young people in the United States. This holiday season we should take the opportunity to educate people in our communities about this fact and encourage them to support prevention efforts to make our roads safer. To help you make this point, we have enclosed the following information, adapted from material provided by the National 3D Prevention Month Coalition and the <A HREF="http://www.nhtsa.dot.gov/">U.S. Department of Transportation National Highway Traffic Safety Administration</A>:


<UL>
<LI>a <A HREF="Alcohol_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> that illustrates the extent of drunk driving nationwide and shows the costs of alcohol-related car crashes;
<LI><A HREF="Alcohol_Myths.html">Myths and Truths</A> about alcohol and its effects on driving;
<LI>a <A HREF="Alcohol_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> you can revise and send to your local newspaper;
<LI>a <A HREF="Alcohol_Pitch.html">Cover Letter</A> to include with your Op-Ed;
<LI><A HREF="Alcohol_NoEtOH.html">Non-Alcoholic Drink Recipes</A> you can ask your local newspaper to run in an effort to encourage people to host safe parties this holiday season.  
</UL>


<P><H3>HOW TO USE THIS KIT:</H3>


<OL>
	<LI>Use the <A HREF="Alcohol_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> to illustrate the problem of drunk driving nationwide and to show the cost of alcohol-related car crashes on society. You can also use these facts to make the case that preventing alcohol abuse can save lives in your community.


	<LI>Use the <A HREF="Alcohol_Myths.html">Myths and Truths</A> to counter common misconceptions about alcohol to educate people about the real risks they take when they drink and drive.


	<LI>Tailor the <A HREF="Alcohol_Op-Ed.html">Op-Ed</A> provided to fit your community and try to get it published in your local paper. You can also use the sample cover letter we've included with it, and follow the guidelines we've provided for submitting 
	<LI>Op-Eds.


	<LI>Educate public officials about the link between substance abuse and fatal car crashes and ask them to help raise public awareness about the problem.


	<LI>Schedule an editorial board meeting with your local paper and ask them to write an editorial urging residents not to drink and drive this holiday season. You can invite a prevention specialist to join you and talk about steps parents can take to be sure their teenagers don't drink and drive. You can also ask the newspaper to run the creative non-alcoholic drink recipes we've provided to encourage party hosts to provide non-alcoholic beverages for guests who will be driving. In addition, you might also want to create a list of tips for hosting safe parties. 
</OL>


<P>
We would like to know if these tools are helpful and if you have attracted media attention for your efforts.   Please give us your feedback and any suggestions for improving these kits.  You can call <A HREF="mailto:diane@jointogether.org">Diane Barry</A> or <A HREF="mailto:lisa@jointogether.org">Lisa Falk</A> at Join Together:  (617) 437-1500 or fax us a note at (617) 437-9394.
<p><p>

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER>


</BODY>
