<TITLE>Prevention Works</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>



<H2>Prevention Works</H2>
</center>

Across the country community groups are making great strides in preventing alcohol and drug abuse and the related problems that result. But despite these successes, more remains to be done. In fact, two recent studies suggest that some of the gains we have made in reducing substance abuse are beginning to lessen. This means that we must strengthen the message that prevention works and encourage all sectors of society to join in community-wide efforts. To help you make this point, we have enclosed the following information:

<UL>
	<LI>a <A HREF="Prevention_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> that illustrates how prevention works to reduce substance abuse and provides statistics from two recent studies;

	<LI>a <A HREF="Prevention_Pitch.html">Pitch Letter</A> to interest reporters and editors in prevention and encourage them to do a feature or series looking at various prevention efforts in your community; and

	<LI>a <A HREF="Prevention_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> you can send to your local newspaper -- either as is, or with some local examples added.
</UL>



<H3>HOW TO USE THIS ACTION KIT:</H3>

<OL>
	<LI>Use the <A HREF="Prevention_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> to illustrate that alcohol and drug problems can be prevented. You can use these statistics 	and examples as talking points to get a reporter or editor from your local newspaper to do a feature story 	looking at prevention efforts in your area and what they have accomplished. You can also use these facts to 	interest a local talk radio station to do a show on this topic.

	<LI>Tailor the <A HREF="Prevention_Pitch.html">Pitch Letter</A> with examples of local prevention efforts at work to reduce substance abuse. Use this to interest your newspaper in the topic. Also provide names and phone numbers of youth and adults involved in area prevention efforts who can talk about their experiences. Give examples of the broad range of 	prevention programs out there. 

	<LI>Send the <A HREF="Prevention_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> to your local newspaper and ask them to run it. Call to follow-up after sending it. It is written to be a recruitment piece.

<LI>Educate public officials about the scope of substance abuse problems in your community and the crucial role prevention programs play in reducing them. Provide the findings from the Monitoring the Future study and the 	Harvard School of Public Health study on the second-hand effects of binge drinking in the fact sheet. 	Challenge them to act by supporting local efforts.

<LI>Schedule an editorial board meeting with your local paper and ask them to write an editorial supporting the local prevention efforts and providing action steps that residents can take to help reduce the problem in your area. </OL>


<hr>We would like to know if these tools are helpful and if you have attracted media attention for your efforts. Please give us your feedback and any suggestions for improving Hot Issues. . .  <br>
	You can call <A HREF="mailto:diane@jointogether.org">Diane Barry</A> or <A HREF="mailto:lisa@jointogether.org">Lisa Falk</A> at <A HREF="/">Join Together</A>:  (617) 437-1500 or fax us a note at (617) 437-9394.
