<TITLE>TREATMENT WORKS &amp; WE CAN PROVE IT</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>



<H2>TREATMENT WORKS &amp; WE CAN PROVE IT</H2>
</center>

<P>Several recent credible studies have found that providing substance abuse 
treatment is a cost-effective investment for communities. To get this 
message out to the public and to key groups in your community, we have 
provided you with the following:


<UL>
	<LI>a <A HREF="TXWorks_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> with key findings from the various studies that have been done;
	<LI>a <A HREF="TxWorks_Pitch.html">Sample Feature Story Pitch Letter</A> and a <A HREF="TxWorks_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> article you or your board members can revise and send to your local newspaper;
	<LI>a list of Resources you can contact for more information on the cost of substance abuse and treatment in your area, as well as tips for getting other groups to join your efforts.
</UL>


<P>


<P><H3>HOW-TO USE THIS MONTHLY ACTION KIT AND RECENT TREATMENT STUDIES:</H3>


<OL>
	<LI>Use the <A HREF="TXWorks_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> to make a case for having a similar study conducted in your state or to get publicity for the results, if one has already been done.


	<LI>Use the <A HREF="TxWorks_Pitch.html">pitch letter</a> to interest a health or feature reporter in writing about the treatment capacity, need and effectiveness in your area. Your letter should provide some story ideas and give the reporter the sense that this is an important story and that you can be a major resource for them.


	<LI>Tailor the <A HREF="TxWorks_Op-Ed.html">Op-Ed</a> provided to fit your community and try to get it published in your local paper to educate people about the cost-effectiveness of treatment.


	<LI>Meet with newly elected officials and get reacquainted with incumbents to discuss the importance of adequate and effective treatment capacity in your community.


	<LI>Call the resources listed to get local statistics on the cost of substance abuse in your state and use these numbers, along with the ones provided in our fact sheet, in the <A HREF="TxWorks_Op-Ed.html">Op-Ed</a> and as a guest on talk radio shows to illustrate that treatment works.


	<LI>Schedule an editorial board meeting with your local paper and ask them to write an editorial in favor of providing more public treatment in your state. You can present statistics from the studies that have already been done (included in the fact sheet, pitch letter and op-ed), and also use local ones gathered from the organizations listed under resources. Invite someone from a local treatment facility to join you.


	<LI>Suggest that your local television station do an investigative piece on the cost of substance abuse in your area versus the cost of providing treatment. Present the treatment survey findings from other states, as well as the information you have gathered using our resource sheet, to get them started.
</OL>


<P>


<P>We would like to know if these tools are helpful and if you have 
attracted media attention for your efforts. Please give us your feedback 
and any suggestions for these Hot Issue reports.  
You can call <A HREF="mailto:diane@jointogether.org">Diane Barry</A> or <A HREF="mailto:lisa@jointogether.org">Lisa Falk</A> at <A HREF="/">Join Together</A>:  (617) 437-1500 or 
fax us a note at
(617) 437-9394.

