<TITLE>Homelessness and Substance Abuse</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>



<H2>Homelessness and Substance Abuse</H2></center>


<P>Today, more than seven million people in the United States live on the streets or in shelters because they do not have a home. And nearly half of homeless people suffer from alcohol or drug addictions. These men and women live in our communities. You can help to reduce homelessness by making sure that all Americans have access to the health care they need -- including adequate substance abuse services.


<P>To get this message out to the public and key groups in your community, we have provided you with the following:


<UL>
	<LI>a <A HREF="Homeless_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> with statistics on the problem and how treatment would help;


	<LI>a <A HREF="Homeless_Press.html">Sample Press Release</A> and a <A HREF="Homeless_Sample.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> article you or your board members can revise and send to your local newspaper;


	<LI>a list of <A HREF="Homeless_Resources.html">Resources</A> you can contact for more information on the problem, as well as tips to help you get other groups to join your efforts.
</UL>


<P>How to use these tools:


<OL>
	<LI>Use the <A HREF="Homeless_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> to interest the media in this topic.



<UL>
	<LI>Select compelling statistics to get newspaper, television and radio reporters to care about this issue.


	<LI>Set up an Editorial Board meeting with your local newspaper and use these statistics as talking points to show the link between homelessness and substance abuse. Invite the head of your local homeless shelter and a public treatment provider to share their perspectives. Discuss how access to treatment can help. Encourage the Editorial Board to write in support of substance abuse treatment to  reduce homelessness.


	<LI>Use these facts to write a Letter to the Editor or an <A HREF="Homeless_Sample.html">Op-Ed</A> (see sample included) about the need for alcohol and drug treatment to reduce homelessness.
</UL>


<LI>Use the <A HREF="Homeless_Press.html">Sample Press Release</A> to get press coverage.


<UL>
	<LI>Revise the release by adding local examples of people who are homeless in your area. Send the release to reporters at your local paper with your name and phone number listed as the contact. Call to follow up. Be prepared to suggest story ideas and other contact persons for this topic.
</UL>


<LI>Use the <A HREF="Homeless_Resources.html">Resource Sheet</A> to illustrate the scope of the problem and expand your coalition.


<UL>
	<LI>Call the resources listed to gather more statistics about homelessness nationally, as well as to define the scope of the problem locally. Contact groups listed or others you might know to understand the scope of homelessness in your area and examples of how treatment can help to reduce the problem.

	<LI>Get these groups to join your coalition.
</UL>
</OL>

<P>We would like to know if these tools are helpful and if you have attracted media attention for your efforts. Please give us your feedback and any suggestions for improving A Message Each Month. . . You can call <A HREF="mailto:diane@jointogether.org">Diane Barry</A> or <A HREF="mailto:lisa@jointogether.org">Lisa Falk</A> at Join Together:  (617) 437-1500 or fax us a note at (617) 437-9394.
