<TITLE>SUBSTANCE ABUSE AND OLDER AMERICANS</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
</center>

<BR>


<center>

<H2>SUBSTANCE ABUSE AND OLDER AMERICANS</H2>
</center>

<P>Many people think of substance abuse as a problem that affects only young people. However, many older people also suffer from alcohol and drug addictions. In fact, senior citizens consume a disproportionate amount of prescription and over-the-counter drugs and have a higher risk of becoming dependent on these substances. And some older people drink heavily because they are lonely or bored. It is important that we recognize the dangers of substance abuse among older Americans and offer help to those who need it. To help you educate your community about this problem, we have provided:
 

<UL>
<LI> a <A HREF="Elderly_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> that shows the problem of substance abuse and older Americans and the high cost to taxpayers;
<LI><A HREF="Elderly_Warnings.html">Warning Signs</A> that indicate that drinking may be a problem. You can post these in places where senior citizens congregate;
<LI><A HREF="/JTO/issues/Elderly/Elderly_Resources.html">Resources</A> that you can call to find out more about substance abuse and older people;
<LI>a <A HREF="/JTO/issues/Elderly/Elderly_Press.html">Sample Press Release</A> you can localize to interest your community paper in writing about this important topic;
<LI>a <A HREF="Elderly_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> to send to your local newspaper to educate readers about the problem of seniors abusing alcohol and prescription drugs.
</UL>
 

<H3>HOW TO USE THIS ACTION KIT</H3>
<OL>
<LI>Use the <A HREF="/JTO/issues/Elderly/Elderly_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> and <A HREF="Elderly_Press.html">Sample Press Release</A> to illustrate substance abuse problems among 	older people and to interest your local newspaper in examining the problem. Suggest that a 	reporter interview local doctors and health centers that treat senior citizens. He or she can 	also 	visit the senior center in the community or other places where older people gather and find out 	what activities are available for seniors to keep them active.
<LI>Repackage the <A HREF="Elderly_Warnings.html">Warning Signs</A> of alcohol abuse in older people and run it in your organization's newsletter to alert people to the problem and encourage them to seek help. You can also ask your local newspaper to run this list to educate readers who may have a problem and be unsure where to turn. Another way to use this information is to post it in places that seniors frequent.
<LI>Use the list of <A HREF="/JTO/issues/Elderly/Elderly_Resources.html">Resources</A> provided to find out more about substance abuse and older people and to find out about local organizations that deal with this problem. You can pass this list on to reporters and suggest they call for more information about this topic.
<LI>Revise the <A HREF="Elderly_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> and send it to your local newspaper to alert people to the problem and to raise public awareness.
</OL>
 

<P>	We would like to know if these tools are helpful and if you have attracted media attention for your efforts. Please give us yo ur feedback and any suggestions for improving A Message Each Month... <br>
 You can call<A HREF="mailto:diane@jointogether.org">Diane Barry</A> or <A HREF="mailto:lisa@jointogether.org">Lisa Falk</A> at Join Together:  (617) 437-1500 or fax us a note at (617) 437-9394.
<p>
<p>


