<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Using Join Together's National Survey</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>

<H3><CENTER>HOW TO USE JOIN TOGETHER'S <BR>
THIRD NATIONAL SURVEY FINDINGS</CENTER>
</H3>
<BR>
Substance abuse problems continue to rise in many communities across the
country. Despite increased awareness about this fact, many community groups
report that elected officials -- governors, Congressmen and state legislators
--are LESS involved in communitywide anti-drug efforts today than they were
two years ago. Join Together's third national survey of community anti-drug
efforts conducted July through October, 1995, alerts us to this disturbing
fact. You will receive a full copy of this survey report sometime in December.
In the meantime, we have provided you with this kit to give you a head-start
on using these national findings to raise public awareness about substance
abuse problems in your community. <BR>
<BR>
To help you do this, we have provided you with the following: 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> of the nation's substance abuse
problem; 
<LI><A HREF="highlights.html">Highlights</A> of Join Together's third national
survey of community anti-drug efforts; to give you some action steps to
get businesses, politicians, churches and other groups more involved in
anti-substance abuse efforts; 
<LI>A <A HREF="letter.html">Sample Pitch Letter</A> to entice an editor
to take a look at the scope of alcohol and drug abuse in your community
and how it compares to the scope of theproblem nationally; 
<LI>A <A HREF="release.html">Sample Press Release</A> you can send to the
editor of your local newspaper announcing the national survey findings and
showing how your community compares to others around the nation; 
<LI>A <A HREF="oped.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> you can ask your local newspaper
to run to educate residents about the survey findings and let them know
what is happening in your community. 
</UL>
<BR>
(We would like to know if you have any success using this Kit to get your
local media to run stories about substance abuse and the Join Together national
surveyfindings. Please fax a copy of any news clips to: <A HREF="mailto:lisa@jointogether.org">Lisa Falk</A> at (617)
437-9394. Thanks.)<BR>
<BR>
Date: 11/6/95<BR>
