    <TITLE>YOUTH ACCESS TO TOBACCO</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>

<H2><CENTER>YOUTH ACCESS TO TOBACCO </CENTER>
</H2>
<P><CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<H3><CENTER><A HREF="../../policy/Surveys/CigVender/intro.html">Get the
survey results</A> now!</CENTER>
</H3>
<P><CENTER><HR> </CENTER>
<P>Although it is illegal in all states to sell cigarettes to anyone under
18-years-old, kids have easy access to tobacco products. Each day, three
thousand youngsters in the United States become regular smokers. On an annual
basis, this is about one million youth. And despite our efforts to get the
message out that smoking is hazardous to kids' health, the fact is that
tobacco use by kids continues to rise. In the past three years, smoking
among eighth graders has increased by 30 percent. This finding sends a warning
bell that we must reinvigorate our efforts to keep kids from using tobacco
products. To help you measure the availability of tobacco in your community
and to raise public awareness of this problem, we have provided you with
the following: 
<UL>
<LI>A <A HREF="Tobacco_Project.html">Project Description</A> suggesting
how you can measure tobacco availability near a public school in your community.
<LI>A <A HREF="Tobacco_Facts.html">Fact Sheet</A> showing the scope of underage
tobacco use on the national level. 
<LI>A <A HREF="Tobacco_Worksheet.html">Worksheet</A> you can copy and distribute
to your project team to record the number of outlets selling tobacco in
your designated area. 
<LI>A<A HREF="Tobacco_Results.html"> Results Form</A> you can use to tally
the worksheets. Use the totals as a measure of tobacco availability in your
area and also fax back a copy of this form to Join Together. 
<LI>Suggestions on how to <A HREF="Tobacco_Organize.html">Organize Local
Groups</A> including youth to assist your efforts. 
<LI>A <A HREF="Tobacco_Pitch.html">Sample Pitch Letter </A>to interest your
local newspaper in covering your efforts. 
<LI><A HREF="Tobacco_Action.html">Action steps</A> you can take once you
have determined the extent of the problem locally. 
<LI>A <A HREF="Tobacco_Op-Ed.html">Sample Op-Ed</A> to educate the community
about your findings and encourage people to take action. 
<LI><A HREF="Tobacco_Resources.html">Resources</A> you can call for more
information on the problem or for help devising solutions. 
<LI><A HREF="Tobacco_Others.html">Examples</A> of What Others Have Done
to keep kids from smoking. 
<LI><A HREF="Tobacco_Reading.html">Further Reading</A> to learn more about
this issue and what you can do. 
<LI>Participate in an <A HREF="../../forum/coffee.html">online discussion</A>
about youth access to tobacco. 
</UL>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/MapServe/footer.gif"
WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle CENECASCALEIMAGE="0" ISMAP
