<TITLE>Non-Alcoholic Drink Recipes</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>


<H3>Drinking and Driving</H3>
<H2>Non-Alcoholic Drink Recipes</H2>
</center>

<P>
The following recipes are creative drink alternatives to serving alcohol at holiday parties. You may want to distribute these recipes widely in your community, either through your newsletter or as a handout at a coalition meeting. These drinks are popular among young people as well as adults. Your local newspaper may also be interested in running the recipes for its readers.


<P>


<PRE>Citrus Collins
Fill 10-12 ounce glass with ice cubes
Add: 	2 ounces of freshly squeezed orange or grapefruit juice
	1 ounce of freshly squeezed lemon juice
	1 ounce of simple syrup
	Club soda until the glass is full. 
	

Garnish with half an orange slice and a cherry.



Mai-Tai
In a shaker or tall glass, combine the following:
	1/2 cup of pineapple juice
	1/4 cup of club soda
	1 Tbsp. of grenadine syrup
	1/4 cup of orange juice
	1 Tbsp. of cream of coconut


Shake or stir to blend. Add crushed ice.


Holiday Delight
Blend the following ingredients in a mixer:
	1/2 cup of orange juice
	1/4 cup of frozen strawberries
	1/4 cup of cranapple juice
	1/4 cup of half and half
	1/2 a banana


Pour into a tall glass.



Viennese Coffee
Combine:	
	1/4 cup whipping cream
	1 Tbsp. of powdered sugar
	1/2 tsp. of vanilla extract
Beat until stiff. 

Pour 3 cups of very strong coffee (decaffeinated is fine) into four cups. Float whipped cream mixture on top. Garnish with 1/2 tsp. grated orange peel. Use cinnamon sticks in each cup as servers.



The C&C Express
In a blender, mix on low speed to smooth consistency of the following:
	6 ounces of chocolate chip ice cream
	1/4 cup of brewed expresso coffee
	1/4 cup of half and half
	3 Tbsp. of cream of coconut


Pour into an 8-ounce serving glass. Top with whipped cream and chocolate shavings. Garnish with a cookie and serve immediately.



Sangaree Punch
Combine:
	1 quart of cranberry juice cocktail
	1 cup of grape juice


Chill until serving time. 


When ready to serve, fill glasses with cracked ice. Pour mixture into cups. Garnish each with lemon and orange slices and a maraschino cherry. Makes five servings.



The Natural
Blend:
	1/2 a banana
	6 strawberries
	2 ounces of apple juice
	1/4 of an apple, with the skin
	2 ounces of fresh pineapple
	1/2 a cup of fresh ice.


Serve in a wine glass. Garnish with fresh strawberries.
</PRE>
<p><br>
[<A HREF="Alcohol_Index.html">Back</A> to Drinking and Driving]<p>

