<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Warning Signs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Warning Signs of Inhalant Abuse</CENTER>
</H2>
You may want to send the following list to your local newspaper and ask
the editor to run this to educate readers about the signs of inhalant abuse.
You can also create a poster or flier from this list and distribute to parents,
teachers and youth in your community, and post it in local schools, grocery
stores, churches and recreation centers. <BR>
<BR>
It is important for parents, teachers and young people to know some of the
signs of inhalant abuse, so they can recognize when someone is using household
products to get high. Some effects of inhalants are short-term, and they
vary greatly from product to product.<BR>
 <BR>
Some of the following symptoms listed below, provided by the National Institute
on Drug Abuse, are warning signs that someone may be using inhalants: 
<UL>
<LI>Red, runny eyes or nose 
<LI>Sores around the mouth 
<LI>Chemical breath 
<LI>Drunk, dazed appearance 
<LI>Nausea 
<LI>Loss of appetite 
<LI>Anxiety or irritability 
<LI>Paint or stains on the body or clothing 
<LI>Chronic inhalant abusers are also anxious, easily excited, irritable
and restless. 
<LI>Inhalant withdrawal symptoms include hand tremors, headaches, nervousness
and sweating. 
</UL>
[<A HREF="../Inhalants/Inhalant_Index.html">Back</A> to Inhalants] <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER> 
