<TITLE>SAMPLE PITCH LETTER</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>


<H3>Prevention Works</H3>
<H2>SAMPLE PITCH LETTER</H2></center>


You can take the following letter and localize it to encourage a feature 
reporter at your daily paper to take a look at the treatment system in your 
area. If you don't have a certain reporter in mind, you may want to send it 
to the Editor.<br>
If you wish, you can generate a ready to print letter by filling in the form boxes and pressing [Generate] at the bottom.

<HR>

<P>

<FORM ACTION="Prevention_PitchOutput.nclk" METHOD=POST>

Dear 
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Reporter" VALUE="Editor" SIZE=35>
:<br>


<P>Substance abuse prevention programs in our community are making great strides against alcohol and drug use and the resulting problems -- like violent crime, HIV-infection, domestic violence and fatal car crashes. Fewer young people today drink and use drugs than their counterparts a decade ago as a result of extensive efforts to educate them about the dangers.


<P>But several recent national studies have found this decrease in substance use to be slipping. For instance, the Harvard School of Public Health found that almost half of all college students now binge drink (five or more drinks at a time), and widespread binge drinking creates problems for other students on college campuses throughout the country. And the latest Monitoring the Future Study found that marijuana use is up among 8th, 10th and 12th graders.


<P>In light of these findings and talk in the new Congress to cut prevention funding, now would be an opportune time to take an in-depth look at some prevention programs at work in our community. Some examples of prevention programs are student organizations like Students Against Drunk Driving, after-school activities to keep kids off the streets, workplace programs that educate employees about the dangers of alcohol and drug abuse and public awareness campaigns that get the message out throughout the community.


<P>These programs are really making a difference. By calling attention to these efforts, you can help these programs gain support to increase their effectiveness and create a healthier community.


<P>Please feel free to call me at <INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Phone" VALUE="Phone number"> if you need help getting in touch with some local prevention programs.


<P>Sincerely,
<p>

<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Name" VALUE="Your name" size =35><br>
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Title" VALUE="Your Title"><br>
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Organization" VALUE="Your Organization" SIZE=30><br>
<br>

<p><BR><HR>
<center><INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="Generate a letter">
<INPUT TYPE="reset" VALUE="Clear the letter"><br></center>

</FORM>
[<A HREF="Prevention_Index.html">Back</A>]
<br><br>
