<TITLE>SAMPLE PITCH LETTER</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>

<H3>Treatment Works &amp; We Can Prove It</H3>

<H2>SAMPLE PITCH LETTER</H2>
</center>

<P>
You can take the following letter and localize it to encourage a feature 
reporter at your daily paper to take a look at the treatment system in your 
area. If you don't have a certain reporter in mind, you may want to send it 
to the Editor.<br>
If you wish, you can generate a ready to print letter by filling in the form boxes and pressing [Generate] at the bottom.

<HR>

<P>

<FORM ACTION="TxWorks_PitchOutput.nclk" METHOD=POST>

Dear 
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Reporter" VALUE="Reporter's Name" SIZE=35>
:<br>


<P>In recent months, you may have heard about several national and state 
studies that show that providing alcohol and drug treatment is an effective 
way to reduce health care costs and crime in our communities.


<P>As the holiday season approaches, alcohol and drug problems are often 
exacerbated for many people. Knowing that treatment does work -- and 
knowing where to find it -- is an important first step for many of your 
readers who have alcohol or drug problems.


<P>This is a great time for you to do a feature or even a series on various 
alcohol and drug treatment options available in the area and show how they 
help people to get their lives back on track.


<P>Some angles you might take include looking at the difference between public 
and private treatment services and/or inpatient and outpatient services. 
You might also speak with people who have completed treatment to see the 
impact it had on their lives, as well as with business owners and human 
resource specialists who refer employees with addiction to treatment. (You 
can add or substitute other story ideas here.)


<P>I can help you with these and other facets of stories you may want to 
write. Enclosed is a fact sheet with some key findings from the recent 
studies I mentioned.  I will contact you next week to follow up.


<P>Sincerely,


<P>

<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Name" VALUE="Your name" size =35><br>
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Title" VALUE="Your Title"><br>
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Organization" VALUE="Your Organization" SIZE=30><br>
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="Phone" VALUE="Phone number"><br>

<p><BR><HR>
<center><INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="Generate a letter">
<INPUT TYPE="reset" VALUE="Clear the letter"><br></center>

