<TITLE>Resources</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>


<H3>Domestic Violence and Substance Abuse</H3>
<H2>Resources</H2>
</center>

<P>To learn more about domestic violence and alcohol and drug abuse in 
the United States, you can contact the following groups:


<P><B>National:</B>


<dl>
<dt>National Coalition Against Domestic Violence
<dd>P.O. Box 18749
<dd>Denver, CO 80218
<dd>(303) 839-1852


<DT>Center for the Prevention of Sexual and Domestic Violence
<dd>1914 North 34th Street, Suite 105
<dd>Seattle, WA 98103
<dd>(206) 634-1903


<dt>Drugs &amp; Crime Data Center and Clearinghouse
<dd>1600 Research Boulevard
<dd>Rockville, MD 20850
<dd>(800) 666-3332


<dt>Clearinghouse on Family Violence Information
<dd>P.O. Box 1182
<dd>Washington, D.C. 20013
<dd>(800) 394-3366


<dt>Family Violence Research and -Sexual Assault Institute
<dd>1310 Clinic Drive
<dd>Tyler, TX 75701
<dd>(903) 595-6600


<dt>National Clearinghouse for the Defense of Battered Women
<dd>125 South 9th Street, Suite 302
<dd>Philadelphia, PA 19107
<dd>(215) 351-0010<p>
</dl>


<B>Hotline:</B>  
<dl>
<dt>National Domestic Violence Hotline
<dd>(800) 333-SAFE
</dl>

<P><B>State and Local:</B>

<dl>
<dt>State Department of Public Health (usually the women's health division)
<dt>State Medical Society
<dt>Local Battered Women's programs, organizations and counseling hotlines
<dt>Local District Attorney's office (domestic violence unit)
<dt>Counseling programs for batterers
</dl>

<P><B>Ideas For Action</B>


<P>
<OL>
	<LI>Ask the local and state groups mentioned above to join your coalition.
	<LI>Schedule an editorial board meeting and try to create media interest in the      problem of domestic violence and substance abuse.
	<LI>Schedule talk shows on local radio and television stations about this topic.
	<LI>Meet with reporters interested in women's issues to get them to do an article about the problem.
	<LI>Create a public awareness campaign to educate your community about the link between substance abuse and domestic violence.
</OL>

<p><br>
