<TITLE>RESOURCES</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>

<H3>Homelessness and Substance Abuse</H3>
<H2>RESOURCES</H2></center>


<P>To learn more about homelessness and its relationship to alcohol 
and drug abuse in the United States, you can contact the following 
groups:


<P><B>National:</B>

<dl>
<dt>National Coalition for the Homeless
<dd>1621 Connecticut Ave., NW, 4th Floor
<dd>Washington, DC 20009
<dd>(202) 775-1322
<dd>(This coalition can provide you with the names of over 150 
regional, state and local advocates across the country.)
<p>

<dt>National Resource Center on Homelessness and Mental Illness
<dd>262 Delaware Ave.
<dd>Delmar, NY 12054
<dd>(800) 444-7415
</dl>

<P><B>State and Local:</B>


<P>

State Welfare Office<br>
Local Salvation Army<br>
Local homeless shelters<br>
Local detox programs for homeless people<br>
Local United Way office<br>


<P><B>Ideas For Action</B>


<OL>
	<LI>Ask local shelter directors to work with you to publicize the scope of homelessness and addiction in your community and the current treatment need and capacity.


	<LI>Invite the state and local groups mentioned above to join your coalition.

	<LI>Schedule an Editorial Board meeting with your major newspaper to create interest about the problem of homelessness and its connection with alcohol and drug abuse. Invite a local shelter director and treatment provider.


	<LI>Ask to be a guest on local radio and television talk shows about this topic.


	<LI>Join with a local shelter director to invite reporters or a T.V. crew to visit their program with you to see first-hand the substance abuse problems that exist in your area.


	<LI>Find some local examples of homeless men and women with substance abuse addictions who have completed treatment and gone on to obtain jobs and their own homes. Use these examples to illustrate how treatment works to reduce homelessness.
</OL>
