<TITLE>SUBSTANCE ABUSE AND OLDER AMERICANS: WARNING SIGNS</TITLE>
</HEAD>


	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>


<BR>

<H3>SUBSTANCE ABUSE AND OLDER AMERICANS</H3>

<H2>WARNING SIGNS THAT DRINKING MAY BE A PROBLEM</H2>
</center>

<P>Many older people who drink do so because they are lonely or bored with their lives. The problem could get worse with time if the person does not receive help. Health care experts say the following warning signs indicate when drinking could be a problem. You may want to repackage this list to include your organization's newsletter; post it at senior centers, your local library or supermarkets; or ask your community newspaper to run it along with a list of local resources people can call for help.


<UL>
<LI>Do you neglect your personal appearance when you drink?


<LI>Do you drink so much you forget to feed your pets and clean your house?


<LI>Do you drink in the middle of the day?


<LI>Do you suffer injuries as a result of your drinking?


<LI>Do you become defensive if someone mentions your drinking?


<LI>Do you seek out people with whom you can drink?


<LI>Do you avoid places where no drinking takes place?


<LI>Do you experience:

<UL>
<LI>a flushed face?
<LI>trembling?
<LI>gaps in memory?
<LI>depression?
<LI>fatigue?
<LI>weight loss?
<LI>aggression?
</UL>


</UL>


<P>If you answered "yes" to one or more of these questions, you may want to:

<UL>
<LI>Talk to a family member or a friend about this problem.
<LI>Call your doctor or local addiction center for help.
<LI>Attend an Alcoholics Anonymous meeting or seek out another self-help group.
<LI>Get help as soon as you can. The problem will only get worse with time.
</UL>


<P>If you would like more information about older people and alcohol, call the American Association of Retired Persons at (202) 434-2200.   


<CENTER>
<A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/MapServe/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle CENECASCALEIMAGE="0"ISMAP ></A>
