<HEAD>
    <TITLE>1995 National Survey: Pitch Letter</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>

<H3><CENTER>SAMPLE PITCH LETTER</CENTER>
</H3>
<BR>
Dear Editor:<BR>
<BR>
Drug use -- and related crime, HIV infections and homelessness -- is on
the risein Stamford, (replace with your community's name) as it is in other
communities around the nation. We issue a call to action to influential
people in our city, particularly elected officials, business leaders and
citizens, to support substance abuse efforts. <BR>
<BR>
A national study conducted by Join Together, a resource center helping communities
fight substance abuse, found that elected officials and business andreligious
leaders received poor marks from more than 4,000 anti-drug groups around
the country for their lack of involvement fighting alcohol and drugs.<BR>
<BR>
I have enclosed some of the survey highlights, which I think will greatly
interest you. As you well know, alcohol and drug-related crime stories often
runon the front page of your newspaper. And hospital and shelter records
in our community detail the frightening scope of AIDS and domestic violence.
<BR>
<BR>
I urge you to take a close look at substance abuse here in Stamford (replace
with your community's name) and see how the problem -- and the commitment
of keyleaders to fight it -- here compares with the rest of the nation.
<BR>
<BR>
You may want to interview youth, parents, teachers and community groups
about their perception of local alcohol and drug abuse problems and ask
them what solutions they suggest. Then you could talk to business leaders
and elected officials and ask them if they are involved in efforts to fight
such problems. Ican suggest some people you can talk with. I can also give
you suggestions of ways more people in the community can help make a difference.<BR>
<BR>
By raising public awareness about the substance abuse problem in Stamford
(replace with your community's name), we can get all the key groups in the
community working together to help fight it.<BR>
<BR>
If you have any questions, you can contact me at (your phone number). <BR>
<BR>
Sincerely,<BR>
<BR>
YOUR NAMEORGANIZATION<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Date:  11/6/95<BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="../../../Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC=
"../../../MapServe/footer.gif" WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=
middle CENECASCALEIMAGE="0"ISMAP ><BR>
