    <TITLE>Tobacco Control: Sample Pitch Letter</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>

<H2><CENTER>Youth Acces to Tobacco<BR>
SAMPLE PITCH LETTER </CENTER>
</H2>
<BR>
<HR><BR>
Dear Editor: <BR>
<BR>
As you know, it is illegal for anyone under 18 to purchase tobacco. Nonetheless,
kids in our community are increasingly beginning to smoke cigarettes by
the ages of 12 and 13. And cigarette smoking is on the rise among kids in
communities like ours across the nation. In fact, a recent University of
Michigan study recently found that smoking by eighth graders has increased
by 30 percent over the past three years. This finding tells us that we need
to do a better job of raising public awareness about the dangers of tobacco
use and in discouraging retailers from illegally selling to youth. <BR>
<BR>
To determine just how available tobacco products are in our neighborhoods,
citizens will be coming together on Saturday, Oct. 7, to count the number
of outlets (stores, gas stations, vending machines, etc.) that sell tobacco
within a quarter-mile radius of Kendall Middle School. (REPLACE WITH YOUR
OWN DETAILS.) Many of these places are easily accessible to kids on their
way to and from school. <BR>
<BR>
We invite you and a photographer from your newspaper to join our efforts.
We will be meeting in front of Kendall at 10 a.m. (REPLACE WITH YOUR OWN
DETAILS.) Our findings will be of great interest to your readers, many of
whom have children and grandchildren in our community. We need your help
in getting the message out that smoking is dangerous to our youth. We also
encourage you to call on retailers to take steps to prevent kids from being
able to buy tobacco products. <BR>
<BR>
I can also put you in touch with some students, parents, former smokers
and health care workers if you are interested in doing a feature or a series
on kids who smoke and why, as well as the risks of such behavior. <BR>
<BR>
We will be I will contact you next week to follow up on this. In the meantime,
if you have any questions, you can call me at (YOUR PHONE NUMBER). <BR>
<BR>
Sincerely, <BR>
<BR>
YOUR NAME<BR>
ORGANIZATION <BR>
<BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/MapServe/footer.gif"
WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle CENECASCALEIMAGE="0" ISMAP
><BR>
<BR>
