    <TITLE>Youth Acces to Tobacco: Action Steps</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<H3><CENTER>Youth Acces to Tobacco</CENTER>
</H3>
<H2><CENTER>ACTION STEPS: </CENTER>
</H2>
<BR>
Once you have documented the availability of tobacco near a public school
in your community, you may want to mobilize other groups to team up with
you to take some of the following steps: <BR>
<UL>
<LI>--Initiate sting operations to pinpoint which stores actually sell tobacco
products to youth under age 18 (which is illegal); 
<LI>--Look at the placement and advertising of tobacco products in stores
to see if they are displayed in places that appeal to youth; 
<LI>--See if stores have proper warnings posted to remind consumers that
it is illegal to sell cigarettes to youth; 
<LI>--Consider providing tobacco retailer training; 
<LI>--Count cigarette advertisements near schools, including posters, billboards
and promotional giveaways; 
<LI>--Ask retailers to sign a pledge promising not to illegally sell cigarettes
to youth; 
<LI>--Ask your city council to ban vending machines; 
<LI>--Get youth involved in all of your efforts. 
</UL>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/MapServe/footer.gif"
WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle CENECASCALEIMAGE="0" ISMAP
><BR>
<BR>
