<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Binge Drinking: Sample Letter</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>

<H2><CENTER>SAMPLE PITCH LETTER </CENTER>
</H2>
<BR>
You may want to send the following sample pitch letter (with local examples)
to an editor or reporter at your local newspaper. <BR>
<HR><BR>
<BR>
Dear Editor: <BR>
<BR>
Did you know that college students drink an estimated FOUR BILLION cans
of beer each year? This is a total of 430 million gallons -- enough to fill
an Olympic-sized pool at every college and university in the country. And
students spend $5.5 billion on alcohol annually (or an average of $466 per
student), which is more than they spend on books, coffee, soda, juice and
milk combined. <BR>
<BR>
Movies, television shows and beer commercials often portray youthful drinking
as an acceptable way for students to fit in and be popular. But for some,
along with this &quot;popularity&quot; comes many hazards. <BR>
<BR>
The fact is that as many as 360,000 of the nation's 12 million undergraduates
will die as a result of alcohol abus. This is more than the number who will
get MAs and PhDs combined. And alcohol abuse is also a major factor in other
campus problems, such as violent crimes, rapes and sexually-transmitted
diseases, including AIDS, despite the fact that it is illegal for anyone
under 21 to drink. <BR>
<BR>
As the summer draws to a close and students start heading back to campus,
you may want to take an in-depth look at the scope of college drinking in
our community and some of the problems that result. I can put you in touch
with some local students to find out about their drinking habits, what alternatives
exist, what they think should be done to curb student drinking and how aware
they are of the risks. I can also connect you with some local experts who
can give you more insight on the problem and suggest some fun college activities
that do not involve alcohol that you can spotlight. <BR>
<BR>
As I'm sure you are aware, this is an important topic and one that ultimately
affects us all. By shining the spotlight on this issue, you can help make
this a safer year for students and the whole community. <BR>
<BR>
You can reach me at <SAMP>(YOUR PHONE NUMBER)</SAMP>. I'll call you next
week to follow up. <BR>
<BR>
Sincerely, <BR>
<BR>
YOUR NAME <BR>
TITLE <BR>
ORGANIZATION 
<P><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC=
"/MapServe/footer.gif" WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER=
"0" ALIGN=middle CENECASCALEIMAGE="0" ISMAP ><BR>
<BR>
</A><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>
| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>
| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR>
