<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Inhalant Facts</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Some Facts About Inhalants</CENTER>
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Inhalants -- including glue, paint and other regular household products
-- are the third most abused substances among 12 to 14-year-olds, after
alcohol and tobacco.<A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">1 </A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>As many as one in every five students in the United States has sniffed
or huffed (inhaled through the mouth) such products as markers, gasoline
and air fresheners by the time they reach seventh grade.<A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">2
</A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Inhalant use is on the rise. The number of 8th graders reporting having
used inhalants at least once in their lifetime rose from 20 percent in 1994
to 22 percent in 1995. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">3</A> <BR>
<BR>
<LI>One of the greatest dangers is that while many youth admit to sniffing
some toxic items, they do not consider this to be inhalant abuse. These
products are easily available, free or inexpensive, legal and may give a
pleasurable effect by depressing the central nervous system. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">4
</A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Today, young people and adults abuse more than 1,000 common products.
These inhalants are dangerous chemicals that are not intended for human
consumption, and they do irreversible damage to the human body when misused.
<A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">5 </A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>People who abuse inhalants on a regular basis put themselves at risk
for permanent and severe brain damage. This is because the human brain is
composed of about one-third fatty tissue. Inhalant vapors react with these
fatty tissues by literally dissolving them. Therefore, chronic inhalant
abusers may permanently lose the ability to perform everyday tasks like
walking, talking and thinking. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">6</A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Sudden Sniffing Death syndrome frequently occurs when someone inhales
high concentration aerosol sprays, model airplane glue and spot removers.
These items emit especially toxic fumes absorbed by the brain cells, kidneys,
liver and bone marrow. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">7</A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Inhalant use often leads to other illicit drug use. Youngsters may try
inhalants first because they are legal, easy to get, inexpensive and difficult
to detect. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">8 </A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Because the chemicals in inhalants enter the lungs in such high concentrations,
they can have a more toxic affect than any other type of abused drug. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">9
</A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Each year, hundreds of children die from inhalant use, yet many parents
and educators remain ignorant of this silent epidemic. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">10
</A><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Nearly nine out of 10 parents say they would be very surprised if they
found out their children were using inhalants. <A HREF="Inhalant_Sources.html">11
</A><BR>
</UL>
[<A HREF="../Inhalants/Inhalant_Index.html">Back</A> to Inhalants] <BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER> 
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
