	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/forum.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/forum.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A></CENTER><P><CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/jto/forum/coffee.html">Coffee House</A> | <A HREF="/jto/forum/lists/email.html">EmailLists</A> | <A HREF="/jto/forum/jtolink/links.html">Links</A></FONT></CENTER>

<CENTER><H2>Subabuse:
<BR>
Join Together's National Discussion List
</H2></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE><B>Description</B><BR>
Subabuse, the electronic mailing list operated by Join Together, has become
a major avenue of discussion, collaboration and technical assistance for
hundreds of organizations and individuals across the nation. Subscribers
routinely post questions, answers and comments about community-based efforts
to reduce substance abuse. In addition, Join Together's technical assistance
staff monitors Subabuse traffic and frequently responds to queries via the
list. <BR>
<BR>
<B>Purpose</B><BR>
Participation in Subabuse is not open to the general public.  The purpose
of Subabuse is to support community organizations involved in the planning,
funding and management of substance abuse prevention and treatment programs.
 Subabuse is designed for peer-to-peer interaction between professionals
who are working to strengthen community-based prevention and treatment programs.
 For this reason, we restrict participation in Subabuse discussion to such
individuals.<BR>
<BR>
Other areas of Join Together Online, such as the <A HREF="/JTO/forum/coffee.html">Coffee
House</A>, are broader in focus and provide opportunities for group interaction
for anyone visiting our site.  In addition, many of the discussion lists profiled in <A HREF="otherlists.html">Other
mailing lists</A> are open to anyone.<BR>
<BR>
<B>Sample the Content!</B><BR>
We archive the discussion on Subabuse at our gopher site. Take a few minutes
to <A HREF="/go.qry?gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org:7003/11/idea/subabuse">browse recent
posts</A> to the list from your colleagues across the nation. Doing so will
give you an idea of the kind of questions, answers and ongoing discussion
on Subabuse.  It may also help you determine whether to request a subscription yourself. <BR>
<BR>
You may also do a full-text <A HREF="gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org:2998/7JT-TALK-SUBABUSE">search
of all posts</A> to look for a specific topic that's been discussed. In
fact, we recommend that you conduct a quick search of the Subabuse archives
prior to mailing a new question to the mailing list; you might be surprised
to see that it has already come up before.<BR>
 <BR>
<B><A HREF="subscribe.html">How To Subscribe</A></B><BR>
Instructions for requesting a subscription to Subabuse.
<BR>
<BR>
