    <TITLE>Substance Abuse Mailing Lists</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/forum.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/forum.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A></CENTER><P><CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/jto/forum/coffee.html">Coffee House</A> | <A HREF="/jto/forum/lists/email.html">EmailLists</A> | <A HREF="/jto/forum/jtolink/links.html">Links</A></FONT></CENTER>

<H2><CENTER>Substance Abuse Related Mailing Lists</CENTER></H2>
<P>


<BLOCKQUOTE><P>The following is a list of substance abuse-related mailing
lists
maintained
by other organizations. To subscribe to one of these lists, click on the
highlighted address to bring up an email
dialog box.  In the body of the email, type the following:<BR>
<BR>
subscribe <B>listname yourname</B><BR>
<BR>where <B>listname</B>is the name of the mailing list and
<B>yourname</B> is
your first and last name. <BR>

<BR>A few of the lists use slightly different protocols, which are noted
in
their descriptions below.  See
<A HREF="about.html">about mailing lists</A>
for more detailed instructions. If your browser does not support mailto,
just
send your subscription request as above
to the highlighted "<I>subscribe</I>" address. <BR>

<BR>
Like much on the Internet, mailing lists tend to come and go faster than
we can keep track of them. Therefore, we cannot guarantee that all of
this
mailing lists are still operating, although we have done our best to
maintain
current information.  Please send additions or corrections to <A
HREF="mailto:eric@jointogether.org">eric@jointogether.org</A>.<BR>
<BR>
<HR><B>Addict-L</B> <BR>
Academic and scholarly discussion of addiction related topics (very
active).
<BR>
<I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:listserv@kentvm.kent.edu">listserv@kentvm.kent.edu</A> <BR>
<BR>
<B>AISESNet_Alcohol<BR>
</B>American Indian Science and Engineering Society, discussion of
Native
American drug and alcohol use. <I>Subscribe</I>: <A
HREF="mailto:listproc@listserve.umt.edu">listproc@listserve.umt.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Alcohol</B><BR>
Alcohol &amp; Drug Studies. <I>Subscribe: </I><A
HREF="mailto:listserve@lmuacad.bitnet">listserve@lmuacad.bitnet</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Alcohol-Psychol<BR>
</B>Forum for those who have a research interest in the psychological
processes
surrounding alcohol consumption. <I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:mailbase@mailbase.ac.uk">mailbase@mailbase.ac.uk</A>
(outside U.K); <A
HREF="mailto:mailbase@uk.ac.mailbase">mailbase@uk.ac.mailbase</A>
(inside
U.K.).<BR>
<BR>
<B>APADiv50-forum</B><BR>
For members of the American Psychological Association Division 50
(Addictive
Behaviors). <I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:listserv@csd.uwm.edu">listserv@csd.uwm.edu</A><BR>
<B><BR>
ATHG</B><BR>
Alcohol Temperance History Group. <I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:listserv@miamiu.acs.muohio.edu">listserv@miamiu.acs.muohio.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>BACCHUS</B><BR>
Boost Alcohol Consciousness Concering Health of University Students.<I>
Subscribe: </I><A
HREF="mailto:listserv@ricevm1.rice.edu">listserv@ricevm1.rice.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>DRCTalk</B><BR>
Drug control reform discussion list (very active). <I>Subscribe: </I><A
HREF="mailto:listproc@dcrnet.org">listproc@dcrnet.org</A><BR>
<B><BR>
Drug-Misuse-Research<BR>
</B><I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:mailbase@mailbase.ac.uk">mailbase@mailbase.ac.uk</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Drugabus</B><BR>
Drug Abuse Education, Information and Research. <I>Subscribe</I>:<A
HREF="mailto:listserv@list.ab.umd.edu">listserv@list.ab.umd.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Drughied</B><BR>
Drug abuse research and prevention in higher education.
<I>Subscribe:</I>
<A HREF="mailto:listserv@tamvm1.bitnet">listserv@tamvm1.bitnet</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>EA</B><BR>
Employee Assistance Counselor's Network. This list is managed by
Majordomo
software. In the message line, put your email address instead of your
own
name. <I>Subscribe: </I><A
HREF="mailto:ea-request@webcom.com">ea-request@webcom.com</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>I-A-S-G</B><BR>
Internet Addiction Support Group. This list is managed by Majordomo
software.
In the message line, put your email address instead of your own name.
<I>Subscribe:</I><BR>
<A HREF="mailto:listserv@netcom.com">listserv@netcom.com</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>INCASE</B><BR>
International Coalition of Addiction Studies Educators.  Manual
subscription:
to join, send email to Janet Feenstra, membership secretary at <A
HREF="mailto:jfeenstra@mail.chippewa.tec.wi.us">jfeenstra@mail.chippewa.tec.wi.us</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>INFODRO</B><BR>
The Institute for the Study of the Addictions (a non-profit organization
from Spain) maintains this list, <B>in spanish</B>, about drug addiction
for
those who work with drug addiction people and speak spanish. To
subscribe, send
e-mail to:<A HREF="mailto:servidor@gc.step.es">servidor@gc.step.es</A>
with the
line "sub infodro" in the message.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>IRGGANET<BR>
</B>International Research Group on Gender and Alcohol.  Participation
is
restricted.  <I>Subscribe: </I><A
HREF="mailto:listserv@vm1.nodak.edu">listserv@vm1.nodak.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>ODAAT</B><BR>
One Day at a Time discussion list, open to anyone recovering from
addiction,
abuse, mental illness, etc.  <I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:listproc2@bgu.edu">listproc2@bgu.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>RIA-L</B><BR>
Recovery in Action Discussion List.  This list is managed by Majordomo
software.
In the message line, put your email address instead of your own name.
<I>Subscribe:
</I><A HREF="mailto:listserv@netcom.com">listserv@netcom.com</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>SexAdd-L<BR>
</B>Discussion of research and clinical topics on sexual addiction. 
<I>Subscribe</I>:
<A
HREF="mailto:listserv@kentvm.kent.edu">listserv@kentvm.kent.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Slfhlp-L<BR>
</B>For internatioinal researchers in self-help, including current
projects,
methodologies, and theories.  <I>Subscribe</I>: <A
HREF="mailto:listserv@uiucvmd.bitnet">listserv@uiucvmd.bitnet</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Smoke-Free</B><BR>
Support group for people who are quitting smoking (very a ctive). 
<I>Subscribe:</I>
<A HREF="mailto:listserv@ra.msstate.edu">listserv@ra.msstate.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Solution</B><BR>
SOLUTION is a support and self-help internet mailing list for creating
life changes. Virtually any topic related to making changes in any area
of life is permitted. Sample topics include changing habits (e.g.,
procrastinating), moods (e.g., depression), behaviors (e.g.,
overeating), thinking patterns (e.g., obsessing), and addictions (e.g.,
drinking). <I>Subscribe:</I><a
href=mailto:LISTSERV@sjuvm.stjohns.edu>LISTSERV@sjuvm.stjohns.edu</a>.<BR>
<BR>


<B>Tobactalk<BR>
</B>From the University of Arizona Program for Nicotine and Tobacco
Research.
 Discussion of research and clinical issues.  <I>Subscribe:</I><A
HREF="mailto:listserv@listserv.arizona.edu">listserv@listserv.arizona.edu</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>12Step</B><BR>
Discussion of 12-step programs from Alcoholics Anonymous, Al-Anon,
Overeaters
Anonymous, etc.  <I>Subscribe:</I> <A
HREF="mailto:suhre@trwrb.dsd.trw.com">suhre@trwrb.dsd.trw.com</A><BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="subabuse.html">Subabuse</A></B><BR>
the mailing list maintained by Join Together . Browse current discussion
and even sign up online!</BLOCKQUOTE>
