<HEAD>

<TITLE>Untitled</TITLE>


</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/forum.map"><IMG
SRC="/Mapserve/forum.gif"
WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A></CENTER>

<CENTER><H2>JTO Link</H2>

<H3>Keyword Search Tips</H3>
</CENTER>

Keyword search only looks at two things: the <B>title</B> of the web sites in our database and the paragraph <B>summary</B> of each site.  It is not a search of all topics covered in any given web site. Presently, you can enter only <B>one keyword</B> in your search. <BR><BR>


If your keyword search doesn't turn up anything, try:

<UL TYPE=DISC>
	<LI>Returning to <A HREF="/jto/forum/jtolink/links.html">JTO Link</A> and browsing through the categories that best describe the kind of information you need, or<BR><BR>

	<LI><A HREF="/jto/searchweb.html">Searching the full text</A> of selected Web sites indexed at Join Together by our web robot.  Though it only covers selected sites, this tool is much more powerful since it quickly searches every page our robot finds on the sites--over 13,000 documents in all!

</UL>
