<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Community Exchange In Action</TITLE>
</HEAD>	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/community.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/community.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><P></A><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/jto/community/community.html">Community Action</A> | <A HREF="calendar.html">Events</A>| <A HREF="/jto/community/resource.html">Resource Center</A> | <A HREF="/jto/community/treatment.html">Treatment</A> | <A HREF="/jto/community/comex.html">COMEX</A>| <A HREF="/jto/forum/jtolink/links.html">Links</A></CENTER></FONT>
<H2><CENTER>Community Exchange In Action</CENTER>
</H2>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Below are stories from some of the <A HREF="comex.html">Community Exchanges</A> sponsored by Join
Together:<BR>
<B> <BR>
Community Prevention Network of Western New York <BR>
Amherst, New York</B>
<blockquote><B>Impact:</B>  Fewer minors will be served alcohol in Amherst, N.Y.,
thanks to a new partnership between police and alcohol servers in that suburb
to keep youth from using fake identification. This collaboration resulted
from the Join Together Community Exchange, which spurred involvement of
religious, business and criminal justice representatives in communitywide
substance abuse efforts. The Exchange also brought Amherst and the nearby
city of Buffalo together to host a one-day joint event to raise public awareness
about drug abuse. Called &quot;Take A Stand Against Drugs,&quot; the event
brought families from both municipalities out onto street corners to express
their support for anti-drug efforts.
</blockquote>
<B>Rural Neighbors in Partnership <BR>
Tallahassee, Florida </B>
<blockquote><B>Impact</B>: Kids in Tallahassee will get a healthier start to life,
thanks to a $10,000 grant from the state of Florida to start a church-based
health program for residents there. This grant was just one outcome of the
Join Together Community Exchange. In addition, the youth committee of the
Center for Substance Abuse Partnership found a home through the 4-H Club.
This merger will provide the club with permanency and leadership development
opportunities for its members.
</blockquote>
<B>Community Partnership Program in Arecibo <BR>
Arecibo, Puerto Rico </B>
<blockquote><B>Impact</B>:  The Join Together Community Exchange in Arecibo planted
valuable new roots in that Puerto Rican community. First, the Exchange brought
business leaders in Camuy and Barcelonita; together to form a coalition.
Second, it established new alliances among the Governor's Public Safety
Office, Partnership with Drug-Free America, the National Guard and others
that led to three new federal grants to sustain their efforts. Third, it
sparked a regional collaborative strategic plan with close to 300 participants
to address substance abuse. And finally, it helped the Arecibo Community
Partnership Program expand into three other neighboring communities to strengthen
its efforts.
</blockquote>

<B>Alliance for Substance Education - BASE <BR>
Belleville, New Jersey Belleville </B>
<blockquote><B>Impact:</B>  Anti-substance abuse efforts are making headlines in Belleville,
N.J., a small town outside of New York City. The editor of the local paper
there has committed to run a weekly column on the Belleville Alliance for
Substance Education's activities. This was one of many positive outcomes
of the Join Together Community Exchange, which served to revitalize residents
by recognizing them for their outstanding efforts. The Exchange also raised
awareness about alcohol and drug problems -- and solutions -- among all
sectors of the community, including students, parents, religious leaders,
businesses and health care workers. In addition, minors will have a tougher
time getting alcohol, as the result of a local ordinance established by
elected officials. And youth may have a new place to hang out, because the
town is considering turning a public building into a youth center on weekends.
</blockquote>
<B>Regional Office of Education &amp; Junior League of Kankakee County <BR>
Kankakee, Illinois </B>
<blockquote><B>Impact:</B> Drug offenders in Kankakee can now choose treatment instead
of jail, thanks to a new drug court there. This program is the result of
linkages between the criminal justice system and the community that were
strengthened during the Join Together Community Exchange. Another outcome
is the involvement -- for the first time ever-- of the inter-faith community
in substance abuse issues. This collaboration has led to the creation a
new task force to find strategies to racial/cross-cultural tensions in the
community.
</blockquote>
<B>Safe Streets Coalition <BR>
Tacoma, Washington </B>
<blockquote><B>Impact:</B>  Workers in Tacoma, Wash., may need to take less sick days
as a result of a new focus on wellness among small businesses there. The
Join Together Exchange sparked the development of a task force on youth
and workplace health. The Exchange also led to the creation of a union-based
alliance with the County Labor Council, the Chamber of Commerce; 80 small
businesses, large companies and labor unions. Members have started a workplace
food collection drive and are developing a resource guide to substance abuse
in the workplace.
</blockquote></BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER>
</BODY>
