<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Footnotes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<IMG SRC="takeactionSM.gif" ALIGN=left><BR>

<Center><H1><I><B>Take Action - </B></I></H1>
<H3>on 5 Policies America Must Adopt to <BR>
Reduce and Prevent Substance Abuse</H3>

<A HREF="intro.html">Introduction</A> | <A HREF="participants.html">Participants</A> | <A HREF="TakeAction.html">Take
Action</A> | <BR>
<A HREF="one.html">One</A> | <A HREF="two.html">Two</A> | <A HREF="three.html">Three</A>
| <A HREF="four.html">Four</A> | <A HREF="five.html">Five</A> | <A HREF="CallToAction.html">Call for Action</A> | <A HREF="steps.html">Action Steps</A> | Notes</Center>


<BR><BR Clear=left>

<BR><BR>

<H2>Footnotes</H2>
<FONT SIZE="-1">1 RAND Corporation, Drug Policy Research Center. Controlling Cocaine: Supply
Versus Demand Programs, 1994.<BR>
<BR>
2 State of California Department of Alcohol and Drug Programs and the National
Opinion Research Center. Evaluating Recovery Services: The California Drug
and Alcohol Treatment Assessment (CALDATA), April 1994. p. 33.<BR>
<BR>
3 Swartz, James A., Lurigio, Arthur J. and Slomka, Scott A. The Impact of
IMPACT: An Assessment of the Effectiveness of the Cook County Jails Substance
Abuse Treatment Program. Chicago, IL, 1994.<BR>
<BR>
4 Join Together. Fixing a Failing System; National Policy Recommendations:
How the Criminal Justice System Should Work With Communities to Reduce Substance
Abuse, Feb. 1996.<BR>
<BR>
5 Toward More Sensible Drug Control Policies: Priorities For A National
Working Group. Harvard University, The Mind/Brain/Behavior Interfaculty
Initiative, Drugs and Addiction Working Group, May 1996.<BR>
<BR>
6 Chaloupka, Frank, J. &quot;Effects of Price on Alcohol-Related Problems,&quot;
Alcohol Health and Research World, Vol. 17. No. 3. U.S. Department of Health
and Human Services, 1993.<BR>
<BR>
7 Hingson, R., Strunin, L. and Berlin, B. Five Years After Surgeon General
Koop Called for Adolescent AIDS Education: Have Teen Beliefs and Behaviors
Changed? A Massachusetts Study, 1993.<BR>
<BR>
