<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Letter to Editor</TITLE>


</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<H2>Sample Letter to The Editor</H2>
</CENTER>
<I>You can tailor the following Letter to the Editor with local statistics and send it to the editorial page editor of your local newspaper.

</I><BR><BR>

Dear Editor:
<BR><BR>
Our kids are buying alcohol, despite the fact that the legal drinking age is 21. This is particularly alarming when you consider that alcohol is a leading cause of death among young people.
<BR><BR>
April is Alcohol Awareness Month and this is an opportune time to call attention to the serious problem of underage drinking in our community. Consider the following facts:<BR>
<BR>
--Bars and stores do sell alcohol to minors.
<BR>
--High school students consume 31 million gallons of wine coolers and 102 million gallons of beer each year.
<BR>
--Nearly half of all college students who have been the victim of a crime had been drinking when it occurred.
<BR>
--Most students do not know that if they drink too much too quickly, they can die of an alcohol overdose.
<BR>
--Drinking is associated with other causes of death among youth -- including car crashes, murders and suicides.
<BR><BR>
It is time our community comes together to reduce and prevent underage drinking. We must get the message out in our schools, our homes and in our businesses that we will not tolerate sales of alcohol to minors. This is an important step in keeping our kids safe.

<P>For more information on how you can help make a difference, contact (INSERT YOUR NAME) at (INSERT YOUR PHONE NUMBER).
<BR>
<BR>
Sincerely,<BR><BR>

Your Name
<BR>Your Organization
<BR>
