<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>What You Can Do</TITLE>


</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<H2>What You Can Do</H2>
</CENTER>
Here are some suggestions you might want to use during Alcohol Awareness Month or any other time of the year when you
would like to devise solutions to alcohol problems in your community.
<UL>
<LI>Ask grocery stores to provide quantities of grocery bags to schools and ask students to illustrate these bags with
Alcohol Awareness Month messages. Return the illustrated bags to the stores for use with customers during April. 

<LI>Use liners in school cafeteria trays to promote Alcohol Awareness Month.

<LI>Establish a "homework place" for middle school students whose parents work during the day. Having a place to go
with adult supervision can help kids resist peer pressure. High-school students can serve as mentors, and
corporations can donate equipment like computers and arts and crafts supplies.

<LI>Enlist local parents to pledge that they will not serve alcohol to minors in their homes.

<LI>Review school rules regarding use of alcohol and see if they are adequately enforced.

<LI>Organize an alcohol awareness rally or parade.

<LI>Enlist local artists to paint murals illustrating alcohol-related issues that are of specific concern to your
community.

<LI>Offer public recognition to young people who lead drug-free lifestyles.

<LI>Insert a list of self-help groups and local resources with public utility bills.

<LI>Sponsor an essay/poster contest to address the question: "Is alcohol affecting the quality of life of our young
people?"

<LI>Ask churches and temples to integrate alcohol issues into their ongoing religious classes for young people.

<LI>Ask religious groups and recreation centers to assemble an Alcohol Awareness Month bulletin board. Ask people to
bring in news clippings of alcohol-related incidents in your community. Tell them to look for mentions of alcohol
particularly in crime stories.
</UL>
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
