<HEAD>

<TITLE>How to Use this Kit</TITLE>


</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<H2>How to Use This Kit</H2>

</CENTER>
Consider these facts:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Alcohol abuse is a leading cause of death among youth. This is because drinking is often linked to fatal car
crashes, homicides and suicides. (Centers for Disease Control, 1990.)

<LI>Youngsters typically try their first alcoholic drink around the age of 13. (US Department of Health and Human
Service, 1990.)

<LI>Junior high and high school students drink more than a third of all wine coolers sold in the United States. (HHS)

<LI>The legal age to purchase alcohol in all 50 states is 21. Yet teens have easy access to alcoholic beverages in our
communities. (Office of the Inspector General)

<LI>Two-thirds of all youth who drink say they can buy their own beer (OIG)

<LI>More than 30 percent of youth under the age of 18 in long-term, state-operated juvenile institutions in 1987 were
under the influence of alcohol at the time of their arrest. (US Department of Justice)

<LI>More than half of students in grades five through 12 say that alcohol advertising encourages them to drink. (The
Scholastic/CNN Newsroom Survey on Student Attitudes About Drug and Substance Abuse.)
</UL>

Use this material to get the message out that it is time to Draw The Line against underage drinking. 
<BR>
<BR>
You may also order NCADD's more comprehensive 1996 Alcohol Awareness Month Kit, complete with an organizer'sguide, sample press materials, camera ready art and a sample copy of a new guide for parents called, "What Should I
Tell My Child About Drinking?". The cost for this NCADD Kit is $10 to cover production costs and mailing. 
<BR><BR>
NCADD provides education, information, help and hope in the fight againt the chronic and often fatal disease of
alcoholism and other drug addiction. To order or for more information, call (212) 206-6770.<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER>

</BODY>
