<H2><A HREF="/news/releases/Show_News.qry?News_uid=9166"><IMG SRC="/gif/cadca.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0></A><CENTER>National Results Summary</CENTER></H2>
<B><FONT SIZE="4"><CENTER>Page 1</CENTER></FONT></B><BR CLEAR=ALL>

<BR><IMG SRC="response.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH="123" HEIGHT="110"><B>Response Rate</B><BR>Of the approximately 1,000 candidates CADCA surveyed, 44.3% responded.<BR CLEAR=ALL>


<IMG SRC="quest1.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="135" HEIGHT="135"><B>QUESTION 1<BR></B>
Candidates were asked to prioritize six anti-drug activities according to their perceived importance to reducing the drug problem in this country. The following tabulation shows what percentage of the candidates ranked each of the six activities as number one.<BR>

A. Prevention Programs - 65% <Br>
B. Treatment Programs - 9%<Br>
C. Domestic Supply Reduction - 7% <Br>
D. Law Enforcement For Illegal Use - 7%<Br>
E. Interdiction/Source Country Supply Reduction - 9% <Br>
F. Law Enforcement For Illegal Sale - 3%<BR CLEAR=ALL><BR>

<IMG SRC="quest2.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH="132" HEIGHT="134"><B>QUESTION 2:</B><BR>
Candidates were asked if they opposed or supported the legalization of drugs. Those who answered in favor of legalization were then asked to indicate which drugs should be legal: marijuana, cocaine, heroin, LSD or all drugs. Of the 13% favoring legalization, most limited their support to marijuana.<BR><BR>

OPPOSE LEGALIZATION - 86%<BR>
SUPPORT LEGALIZATION - 13% <BR>
NOT SURE - 1%<BR CLEAR=ALL><BR>

<IMG SRC="quest3.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="154" HEIGHT="168"><B>QUESTION 3</B><BR>
Since the drinking age was uniformly increased to 21, alcohol-related traffic deaths have decreased substantially. Candidates were asked if they support maintaining age 21 as the national legal drinking age. <BR>
<BR>SUPPORT MAINTAINING AGE 21 AS THE DRINKING AGE - 85% <BR>
OPPOSE MAINTAINING AGE 21 AS THE DRINKING AGE - 11% <BR>
NOT SURE - 4%<BR CLEAR=ALL>

