<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Overview</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>What Are Inhalants?</CENTER>
</H2>
Today, more than 1,000 legal and useful household, school and office products
are being used--primarily by youth--to get high. This practice is commonly
known as inhalant abuse. <BR>
<BR>
<B>Inhalants are divided into the following four categories: </B>
<UL>
<LI>Volatile gases and solvents -- lighter fluid, barbecue grill gas, spray
paint, paint thinner and glue. <BR>
<BR>
<LI>Aerosols -- hair spray, deodorants and other pressurized products that
are used more for the propellant capability than for the contents inside
the can. <BR>
<BR>
<LI>Nitrates -- Butyl nitrites, which are often known by the trade names
of Rush, Locker Room, Bolt and Climax and are used as room odorizers; and
amyl nitrates, which are packaged in capsules known as poppers and snappers
and were originally created for heart patients. <BR>
<BR>
<LI>Anesthetic gases -- Nitrous oxide, which is known as the dentists laughing
gas is also available in small cylinders called whippets, which propel whipped
cream in commercial machines. 
</UL>
<B>These substances are abused in the following ways: </B>
<UL>
<LI>Sniffing -- Breathing in the substances vapors through the nose. A youngster
may sniff a container of white out, glue, paint thinner or gasoline to inhale
the fumes through the nostrils. <BR>
<BR>
<LI>Huffing -- Breathing in the substances vapors through the mouth. A student
can spray paint on a handkerchief and hold it over his or her mouth and
breath in the fumes. <BR>
<BR>
<LI>Bagging -- Inhaling the vapors through a bag. A youth can spray fumes
on a cloth or piece of clothing, then insert it into a plastic or paper
bag to increase the concentration of the vapors. Then he or she puts the
bag opening over the mouth or nose and breathes in. Some users may also
place their heads directly inside the bag. 
</UL>
<BR>
[<A HREF="../Inhalants/Inhalant_Index.html">Back</A> to Inhalants] <BR>
<BR>
