<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG SRC="../../../../jto/store/documents/lead.gif" WIDTH="271" HEIGHT="381" ALIGN=left 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">
<H2>Leading from <BR>the Ground Up:</H2><B>
The Third National Survey of 
the Community Movement Against Substance Abuse</B>

<B><A HREF="HillLetter.html"><BR>
<BR>
Letter from Calvin Hill</A><BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="Acknowledge.html">Acknowledgements</A><BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="Summary.html">Summary</A></B><BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="one.html">Section One</A></B>: 
Coalitions - a growing and important force in communities<BR><BR>
<B><A HREF="two.html">Section Two</A></B>: 
Coalition Impact <BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="three.html">Section Three</A></B>: 
Community Report Card -
how coalitions rate the performance of major community institutions
<A HREF="four.html"><BR>
<BR>
<B>Section Four</A></B>: 
Public Policy Views of Coalition Leaders
<A HREF="recommend.html"><BR>
<BR>
<B>Recommendations</A>
<A HREF="appendix.html"><BR>
<BR>
Appendix</A></B>
<BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

For ideas on how to use the Third National Survey to raise public awareness, we have prepared an <A HREF="/JTO/issues/National_Survey/into.html">Action Kit</A>, complete with a sample op-ed, a letter to the Editor and a fact sheet.<BR><BR>
