<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Recommendations</TITLE>
</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<H2><CENTER><IMG SRC="gifs/logoSmall.gif" WIDTH="187" HEIGHT="145" ALIGN=
left NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">Leading from the Ground Up:</CENTER>
</H2>
<H3><CENTER>The Third National Survey of <BR>
the Community Movement Against Substance Abuse</CENTER>
</H3>
<P><CENTER><HR><A HREF="title.html">Contents</A> | <A HREF="hillLetter.html">Letter</A> | <A HREF="Summary.html">Summary</A> | <A HREF="Acknowledge.html">Acknowledgements</A>
<BR>
| <A HREF="one.html">One</A> | <A HREF="two.html">Two</A> | <A HREF="three.html">Three</A>
| <A HREF="four.html">Four</A> | Recommendations
| <A HREF="appendix.html">Appendix</A><HR>
<H3>
<br><br>Recommendations</CENTER>
</H3>
The findings of this third survey carry several important messages: 
<UL>
<LI>First, they tell funders of community-based substance abuse coalitions
how important it is to require these groups to have written strategies.
<LI>Second, the results should serve to remind coalitions to take an active
role in shaping public policy on the local, state and federal levels. 
<LI>Third, it is clear that government officials - particularly members
of Congress, governors and state elected officials - need to take a much
more active role in listening - and responding - to coalition leaders. 
<LI>Finally, our findings are a call to action to businesses, the media
and clergy to get more involved in anti-substance abuse coalition efforts
in their communities. Their participation matters. It really can make a
difference. 
</UL>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="../../../../../Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="../../../../../MapServe/footer.gif"
WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP
