<HEAD>

<TITLE>Resources</TITLE>


</HEAD>
	<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/issues.map"><IMGSRC="/Mapserve/issues.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0 ALIGN=middle"ISMAP ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<H2>Free Resources</H2>


</CENTER>

Single copies of the following resources are available free of charge from the National Clearinghouse on Alcohol and Drug Information. Call (800) 729-6686 to order or for a complete catalogue of materials.
<BR><BR>
<B>Changing Lives</B> <BR>Looks at successful programs that have helped prevent alcohol and drug use among youth in communities.
<BR><BR>
<B>College Students and Drinking</B> <BR>(Alcohol Alert #29) Provides statistical overview of problem, analyzes factors associated with heavy drinking, and discusses intervention approaches.
<BR><BR>
<B>Office of the Inspector General Report on Youth and Alcohol</B><BR> Provides the results of a survey of junior and senior high school students  (grades 7-12) to determine how they obtain, view and consume alcohol.
<BR><BR>
<B>Prevention Resource Guides</B><BR> Available on a variety of subjects, including "Secondary School Students," "Elementary Youth," "Youth in Low-Income Urban Environments," and "College Youth." Each guide contains facts and figures, a catalogue of prevention materials, etc.
<BR><BR>
<B>Sobering Thoughts College Newspaper Insert</B><BR> Provides drop-in articles and clip art for college newspapers. Articles include an overview of the impact that alcohol use and abuse has had on college campuses. A collection of short summaries detailing alcohol-related tragedies that have occurred on college campuses is also included, as well as a list of facts about drinking and questionnaire to "test your alcohol IQ."
<BR><BR>
<B>Straight Talk</B><BR> A 10-minute video for middle school students in English and Spanish. Four teenagers talk about why they won't use drugs and share successful measures that they have found to avoid pressures to use alcohol and other drugs. Includes one teen who is a recovering alcoholic and drug user.
<BR><BR>
<B>"Strategies for Preventing Alcohol and Other Drug Problems on College Campuses"</B><BR> Describes how faculty members can become involved effectively in efforts to address drinking problems at colleges and universities.
<BR><BR>
<B>Tips for Teens About Alcohol </B><BR>Brightly-colored brochure provides information and resources.<BR>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/footer.gif"  WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR>Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></CENTER>
