    <HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Alerts</TITLE></HEAD><!-Default-><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/policy.map"><IMG SRC="/Mapserve/policy.gif"WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="75" ALIGN=bottom BORDER="0" ISMAP></A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="/jto/policy/policy.html">Policy</A>| <A HREF="/jto/policy/panel.html">Panels</A> | <A HREF="/jto/policy/surveys.html">Surveys</A> |<A HREF="/news/alerts/Latest_News.qry?MediaAction=True&Summaries=On&Max=7&Last=30">Alerts</A> | <A HREF="/go.qry?gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org:7003/11/pol">Archives</A>| <A HREF="/jto/policy/links.html">Links</A></FONT></CENTER><H1>Action Alert</H1><p><TABLE WIDTH = "90%" CELLSPACING = "0"><TR><TD WIDTH = "60%"><h2>Istook Amendment Reintroduced in the House</h2></TD><TD></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN = "2"><FONT COLOR = "BLACK">From the Alliance for Justice<br><br>January 16, 1997<br><br>For more information, contact: <A HREF="mailto:dlewis@afj.org">Deborah Lewis</A>, Alliance for Justice, (202) 822-6070; Bob Smucker, Independent Sector, (202) 223-8100; <A HREF="mailto:Bassg@rtk.net">Gary Bass</A>, OMB Watch, (202) 234-8494<br><br><b>Istook Amendment Reintroduced in the House</b><br><br>On January 7, 1997, Congressman McIntosh (R-IN) introduced HR 233, a bill to amend the Lobbying Disclosure Act of 1995 to enact an Istook provision. HR 233 states:<DL><DD>(a) GENERAL RULE - An organization described in section 501(c)(4) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 which engages in lobbying activities or affiliated organizations shall not be eligible for the receipt of Federal funds constituting an award, grant or loan.</DL>(B) DEFINITION - For purposes of subsection (a), any 2 organizations shall be considered to be affiliated organizations if the organizations meet anyone or more of the following criteria:<DL><DD>(1) The governing instrument of one such organization requires it to be bound by decisions of the other organization on legislative issues.<br><br>(2) The governing board of one such organization includes persons who-<br>(A) are specifically designated representatives of the other such organization or are members of the governing board, officers, or paid executive staff members of such other organization; and<br>(B) by aggregating their votes, have significant voting power to cause or prevent action on political advocacy issues by the other such organization.<br><br>(3) The organizations - <br>(A) either use the same name or trademark, or represent themselves as being affiliated; and<br>(B) coordinate their lobbying activities or political advocacy.</DL>This bill takes the Simpson Amendment on the Lobbying Disclosure Act to its extreme. The Simpson Amendment prohibits 501(c)(4)'s that receive federal grants from lobbying. However, the Simpson Amendment allows 501(c)(4)'s that receive federal funds to affiliate with organizations that lobby. Specifically, Senator Simpson said on the floor of the Senate that organizations could bifurcate, creating an entity that receives federal funds and another that lobbies. This new bill would prevent this from occurring by prohibiting lobbying by any organizations (such as 501(c)(3)s) affiliated with a 501(c)(4) that receives federal grants.<br><br>Because this bill proposes to amend the Lobbying Disclosure Act it has been referred to the House Judiciary Committee. This is a different Committee than the one Congressman McIntosh sits on and used as a forum for Istook proposals. It is also not the Appropriations Committee where we saw the bulk of the Istook activity in the last Congress.<br><br>At this point, it is not clear that this bill will move, particularly because it would have to go through the Judiciary Committee, which is less than fertile ground for Istook proposals. When we have more information, we will be sure to pass it on.  Until then, if you have any questions, please contact: Deborah Lewis, Bob Smucker or Gary Bass.
<br><br></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><FONT SIZE = "-1"><TABLE WIDTH ="100%"><TR><TD WIDTH="30%"><B>Date:   </B>01/17/1997</TD><TD ALIGN="RIGHT"><b>Source: Join Together Online</TD></TR></TABLE></FONT><P><I>Distributed by <A HREF="http://www.jointogether.org">Join Together Online</A>.</I></P>    <P><CENTER><A HREF="/Mapserve/footer.map"><IMG SRC="/MapServe/footer.gif"WIDTH="441" HEIGHT="27" BORDER="0" ALIGN=middle  ISMAP><BR><BR></A><A HREF="/default.html">JTO</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/index.html">Index</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/search.html">Search</A> | <A HREF="/JTO/comments.html">Comments</A>| <A HREF="/JTO/help.html">Help</A><BR><BR><HR><FONT SIZE="-1">Distributed by Join Together<BR><A HREF="/">http://www.jointogether.org</A></FONT></B></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
